<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41062c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41062c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41062c"> 62(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">spondan</span></span> / spodanomancy / (ashes)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>SPODANOMANCY</mark> &hellip; is performed &hellip; by scattering ashes thickly in some place exposed to the air, and writing therein with the end of a finger any question about which information is needed. The inscribed ashes are then left for the night, and on the following morning the letters that remain legible are made use of as oracles <small> A.E. Waite, <a name="AEWO" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AEWO"><cite title="source">The Occult Sciences</cite></a> (??) 149-50</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
